#: 10815
msgid "\"That was thorough, Ignus, and hasty. I wanted to speak with her.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10816
msgid ""
"This is a woman with fading bruises on her face and arms and a look of "
"despairing longing in her sunken eyes. She might have been pretty once, but "
"those days were long ago.  She turns slowly to face you. Life pours into her "
"features, and the spark of sardonic light that dances in her eyes now makes "
"you wonder if your eyes were deceiving you. \"Welcome to the Smoldering "
"Corpse, scarred man.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10817 10844
msgid "\"Who are you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10818 10845 10878
msgid "\"I'm looking for a journal. Would you happen to have seen it?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10819 10846
msgid "\"What can you tell me about this place?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10820 10848
msgid "\"Who is that burning by the entryway?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10821 10847 10879
msgid ""
"\"I'm looking for a Collector by the name of Pharod. Have you seen or heard "
"of him?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10822 10849
msgid "\"Nothing. Good day.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10823
msgid ""
"This time, Drusilla seems slightly more lively -- at least, you don't catch "
"a glimpse of the despair that you smelled on her the first time you spoke "
"with her. \"'Lo again, traveler.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10824
msgid "\"Hello, Drusilla. I'd like you to answer some questions for me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10825
msgid "\"Hello, Drusilla, and farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10826
msgid ""
"\"I? I am Drusilla. And you must be clueless. Don't ask me how I know that. "
"It just shines off you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10827
msgid "\"Clueless? I think not.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10828
msgid "\"Shines. Right. Answer some questions for me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10829
msgid "\"I don't want to hear it. Especially not from you. Good day.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10830
msgid ""
"\"A journal? Oh, sure. I've kept an eye out for all stray journals. Just in "
"case some scarred man walks into my favorite bar and starts asking about it. "
"Do you ask that of everyone you meet? What a fascinating life.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10831
msgid "\"You have a smart mouth on you, don't you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10832
msgid "\"Just answer my questions and let's get through this.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10833
msgid "\"Far more so than yours, I'd wager.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10834
msgid ""
"\"Here? This is the Smoldering Corpse, though the person smoldering ain't "
"dead yet. He's just keepin' himself alive 'til someone comes along to help "
"him out. Sods who like to see people in pain come here. Fiends like it. "
"Folks who don't much care for bein' bothered come here too... the name alone "
"keeps out most of the berks.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10835
msgid "\"Who is he, anyway?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10836
msgid "\"I understand. Answer some more questions.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10837
msgid "\"Good name for it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10838
msgid ""
"That despair you saw on her face before flits across it again like a black-"
"winged shadow before she masters herself. \"That's Ignus, one of the "
"greatest wizards ever to come out of this slummy excuse for a cesspool. They "
"caught him and they opened a channel to the plane of Fire through him, and "
"now he's just a doorway for it, keepin' himself alive by force o' will "
"alone. If someone could douse him for a few moments, it'd give him his life "
"back again -- but they don't make enough water to do that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10839
msgid "\"What about this decanter? Word has it it's endless.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10840
msgid ""
"\"Someone should be able to find something. Ah, well. Can you answer some "
"more questions for me?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10841 10869
msgid "\"What's your connection to him?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10842
msgid "\"That's too bad. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10843
msgid "\"Aye, traveler? What is it you seek?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10850
msgid ""
"She smirks at you, and her bruises seem almost to fade. \"Whatever you say, "
"dearie.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10851
msgid "\"Whatever. Answer some questions for me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10852
msgid "\"Whatever. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10853
msgid ""
"\"Aye, a smart mouth for a smart head. I ain't the addle-cove you might "
"think, sod. I got a brain on me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10854
msgid "\"If you're so smart, you should be able to answer my questions.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10855
msgid "\"Too bad it's not IN you. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10856
msgid ""
"\"Oh, is that so, aye? Have you ever been in love with a living flame? Have "
"you ever wanted to vanish utterly in the arms of another, to lose yourself "
"in the heat of passion? Your eyes tell me that you wish you had, but you've "
"had no luck. Don't talk to me about fascinating. Scars ain't fascinating. "
"Fights ain't fascinating. Tough ain't fascinating. YOU ain't fascinating.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10857
msgid "\"I don't really see that I need to justify myself to you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10858
msgid ""
"\"Where should I start? I'm immortal, I lose my memory every time I die, I "
"have a floating skull for a sidekick, I'm having experiences that would make "
"most mortals scream their souls out through their eyes, and you're telling "
"me that being in love with a fire is fascinating? That's not fascinating -- "
"it's just crazy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10859
msgid ""
"\"Where should I start? I'm immortal, I lose my memory every time I die, I'm "
"having experiences that would make most mortals scream their souls out "
"through their eyes, and you're telling me that being in love with a fire is "
"fascinating? That's not fascinating -- it's just crazy.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10860
msgid "\"This conversation is over.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10861
msgid ""
"\"No, that'd be too hard, wouldn't it? G'wan. I don't need to talk to you.\" "
"She turns her back on you, dismissing you."
msgstr ""

#: 10862
msgid "\"You haven't seen the last of me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10863
msgid "\"Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10864
msgid ""
"She recoils suddenly, and looks at you more closely. Excitement creeps into "
"her voice. \"You're him, aren't you? You're him!\""
msgstr ""

#: 10865
msgid "\"What do you mean?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10866
msgid "\"No, I'm not. Answer some more questions.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10867
msgid "\"No, I'm not. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10868
msgid ""
"\"He said you'd come! He said you're the one who'll set him free! He spoke "
"to me in a dream and told me that you'd come with an ocean of water to "
"balance him, so he could burn across the planes! Free him! Please, save him!"
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 10870
msgid "\"I'll think about it. Answer some more questions for me, first.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10871
msgid "\"I'll think about it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10872
msgid ""
"\"I was Ignus' lover. We both loved the flame, though he loved it more than "
"I did. But now I watch his beauty as he writhes in the heart of the fire, "
"and I, Drusilla, love them equally.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10873
msgid "\"You're barmy, aren't you? All right, answer some questions for me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10874
msgid "\"You're totally over the edge. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10875
msgid "\"When will you free Ignus?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10876 20700
msgid ""
"\"As soon as I can get this to him. They say this decanter holds an endless "
"supply of water.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10877
msgid "\"Who are you, exactly?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10880
msgid "\"What can you tell me about this tavern?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10882
msgid ""
"\"Yes! Use that on him and he'll be sure to come free! Oh, my Ignus, I await "
"you!\" She pauses for a moment, dread in her eyes. \"Do you know the command "
"word?\""
msgstr ""

#: 10883
msgid "\"Not yet.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10884
msgid "\"Yes, I do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10885
msgid ""
"\"It is the prison for my love, the place where they have kept him cruelly "
"bound over the centuries, the place I have come over the decades to commune "
"with him in his fiery torment. It is the place that has driven me to live "
"beyond my years and beyond my means. I hate this place.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10886 10889 10892 10895
msgid "\"Very well. Answer some other questions.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10887 10890 10893 10896 10899
msgid "\"I understand. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10888
msgid ""
"Her voice practically throbs with a deep ache: \"I was Ignus' lover and he, "
"my beloved. He loved the flame more than me and now he has become the flame "
"-- and because I love him, I love the flame...  but that's all done with "
"now. Now I wait for him to douse himself. I sell what little I have just so "
"I can be near him.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10891
msgid ""
"\"Pharod?\" she snickers. \"The Collector King? You can probably find him "
"and his stinking ilk in the trash warrens on the far side of the Hive. Good "
"luck in getting any answers from him -- he's a sly devil, he is.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10894
msgid ""
"\"Pharod?\" she sneers. \"The Collector King? You can probably find him and "
"his stinking ilk in the trash warrens on the far side of the Hive. He's a "
"sly devil, he is. Not near as sly as my Ignus, though.\""
msgstr ""

#: 10897
msgid ""
"\"I've seen no journal that I can recall. I don't know. Maybe ask some of "
"the Collectors. I don't know!\""
msgstr ""

#: 10898
msgid "\"That's no help. Give me some answers, Drusilla.\""
msgstr ""

#: 20699
msgid "\"What about this decanter of water? Word has it it's endless.\""
msgstr ""

#: 20710
msgid "\"When I get around to it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 20711
msgid ""
"Her eyes brighten even further, if that's possible. \"Then use it! Use it on "
"him now!\""
msgstr ""

#: 20712
msgid "\"In a minute. I need some more answers from you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 20713
msgid "\"That's what I'm about to do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 20714
msgid ""
"\"Then go find it, I implore you!\" She tugs on your sleeve. Her eyes have "
"taken a frantic sheen of madness."
msgstr ""

#: 20715
msgid "\"I will, I will. I need more answers first...\""
msgstr ""

#: 20716
msgid "\"I will. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 3073
msgid ""
"As you approach the woman to talk to her, Ignus' eyes flare up, and before "
"you can stop him, he embraces her. She returns his embrace, losing herself "
"in his flames. She does not cry out. Your last glimpse of her is burned into "
"your memory: Her eyes are full of fiery passion and all-engulfing love. "
"Nothing is left of her -- not even ashes."
msgstr ""

#: 68053
msgid ""
"Drusilla, who stands by the door in the Smoldering Corpse Bar, told me of "
"the man burning over the grill. His name is Ignus, and he was apparently the "
"best mage to come out of the Hive in ages. His rivals opened a channel to "
"the Elemental Plane of Fire through him, and now he keeps himself alive by "
"sheer concentration. A powerful man, indeed..."
msgstr ""
